# Frontend Architecture

## Directory Structure

```
src/
├── api/                    # React Query hooks wrapping Firebase operations
│   └── firebaseApi.ts      # All query/mutation hooks (co-located)
├── assets/                 # Static assets (images, lottie, icons)
│   ├── game/               # Game-related images
│   ├── icon/               # SVG icons
│   ├── lottie/             # Lottie JSON animations
│   ├── rank/               # Ranking page images
│   └── tutorial/           # Tutorial flow images
├── components/             # UI components grouped by feature
│   ├── error/              # Error display components
│   ├── game/               # Game feature components
│   │   └── modal/          # Game-specific modals
│   ├── rank/               # Ranking feature components
│   └── tutorial/           # Tutorial step components
├── firebase/               # Firebase client initialization
│   └── firebaseClient.ts   # App, Firestore, Analytics instances
├── hook/                   # Custom React hooks
│   └── useModal.tsx        # Portal-based modal hook
├── page/                   # Route-level page components
├── shared/                 # Shared infrastructure (Router)
├── styles/                 # Global CSS files
├── types/                  # TypeScript type definitions
└── utils/                  # Pure utility functions and constants
```

### Placement Rules

| What | Where | Example |
|------|-------|---------|
| Route page component | `src/page/` | `Game.tsx`, `Rank.tsx` |
| Feature UI component | `src/components/{feature}/` | `components/game/KickEbul.tsx` |
| Feature-specific modal | `src/components/{feature}/modal/` | `components/game/modal/ResultModal.tsx` |
| Firebase query/mutation hook | `src/api/firebaseApi.ts` | `useSaveScore`, `useGetTopRanks` |
| Custom UI hook | `src/hook/` | `useModal.tsx` |
| Type definitions | `src/types/` | `game.ts` |
| Pure utility functions | `src/utils/` | `rank.ts`, `worry.ts` |
| Static assets | `src/assets/{category}/` | `assets/game/kick.svg` |
| Global styles | `src/styles/` | `index.css`, `animated.css` |

```tsx
// Good ✅ — New game modal goes in components/game/modal/
// src/components/game/modal/NewModal.tsx

// Bad ❌ — Modal placed at top-level components/
// src/components/NewModal.tsx
```

## Component Patterns

### Page Components

Page components in `src/page/` are entry points for routes. They:
- Fetch data (via React Query hooks)
- Manage page-level state
- Compose feature components
- Handle navigation guards

See @src/page/Game.tsx for the established pattern.

```tsx
// Good ✅ — Page component orchestrates child components
const Game = () => {
  const [step, setStep] = useState(0)
  const [gameState, setGameState] = useState<TGameState>({ /* ... */ })

  const gameSteps = useMemo(() => [
    <WorryDump key="worry" handleNextStep={handleNextStep} setGameState={setGameState} />,
    <KickEbul key="kick" handleNextStep={handleNextStep} setGameState={setGameState} />,
    <GameResult key="result" gameState={gameState} />,
  ], [/* deps */])

  return <>{gameSteps[step]}</>
}

// Bad ❌ — Page component with all UI inline (no composition)
const Game = () => {
  // 500+ lines of mixed rendering, state, and logic
}
```

### Feature Components

Feature components in `src/components/{feature}/` receive data and callbacks via props. They should not directly access `localStorage` or navigate — delegate that to the parent page.

```tsx
// Good ✅ — Component receives handler via props
const KickEbul = ({ handleNextStep, setGameState }: Props) => {
  // Internal game logic
  // Calls handleNextStep() when done
}

// Bad ❌ — Component directly navigates
const KickEbul = () => {
  const navigate = useNavigate()
  // Navigates internally instead of letting parent control flow
}
```

### Modal Pattern

This project uses a portal-based modal hook. See @src/hook/useModal.tsx.

```tsx
// Good ✅ — Using the useModal hook
const { Modal, showModal, hideModal } = useModal()

showModal(<ResultModal onClose={hideModal} />)

return (
  <>
    {/* page content */}
    {Modal}
  </>
)

// Bad ❌ — Manual modal state without the hook
const [isOpen, setIsOpen] = useState(false)
{isOpen && <div className="modal-overlay"><ResultModal /></div>}
```

### Props Pattern

- Destructure props in function parameters
- Use inline type annotations for simple components
- Extract `type TProps` when props exceed 3 fields

```tsx
// Good ✅ — Inline type for simple props
const Error = ({ title, text, children }: { title: string; text: string; children?: React.ReactNode }) => {

// Good ✅ — Extracted type for complex props
type TGameResultProps = {
  gameState: TGameState
  initGame: () => void
  nickname: string
  uniqueId: string
}
const GameResult = ({ gameState, initGame, nickname, uniqueId }: TGameResultProps) => {

// Bad ❌ — Undeclared props type with any
const GameResult = (props: any) => {
```

## State Management

This project does NOT use a global state management library. State is managed in three tiers:

| Tier | Tool | Example |
|------|------|---------|
| Server state | React Query | Firestore data (ranks, game content) |
| Page state | `useState` | Game step, game state object |
| Persistent state | `localStorage` | `nickname`, `uniqueId`, `isPlay` (doc ID) |

### localStorage Keys

| Key | Value | Set When |
|-----|-------|----------|
| `nickname` | User display name | Tutorial/onboarding |
| `uniqueId` | User unique identifier | Tutorial/onboarding |
| `isPlay` | Latest game document ID | After score submission |

```tsx
// Good ✅ — Reading localStorage with null check
const nickname = localStorage.getItem('nickname')
if (!nickname) return <Navigate to="/" />

// Bad ❌ — Assuming localStorage always has value
const nickname = localStorage.getItem('nickname')!
```

## Routing

All routes are defined in @src/shared/Router.tsx. When adding a new route:

1. Create the page component in `src/page/`
2. Add the route in `Router.tsx`
3. Use `React.lazy()` for non-critical pages
4. Add a catch-all `*` route already exists for 404

### Route Map

| Path | Page | Lazy |
|------|------|------|
| `/` | `Splash` | No |
| `/tutorials` | `Tutorials` | No |
| `/game` | `Game` | No |
| `/ranking` | `Rank` | Yes |
| `/content` | `Content` | Yes |
| `/special-thanks` | `SpecialThanks` | Yes |
| `*` | `NotFound` | No |

## Layout

The app is wrapped in a mobile-first container (max-width `md`, centered, black background, max-height 900px). See @src/App.tsx.

```tsx
// This layout is defined in App.tsx — do not duplicate it in page components
<div className="min-h-[100dvh] bg-gray-100">
  <div className="mx-auto flex h-[100dvh] max-w-md items-center justify-center bg-white">
    <div className="h-full max-h-[900px] w-full overflow-y-auto bg-black">
      {/* Routes render here */}
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

Page components should fill `h-full` and not set their own max-width or centering wrappers.

```tsx
// Good ✅ — Page fills parent container
<div className="relative h-full">

// Bad ❌ — Page re-creates the centering layout
<div className="mx-auto flex max-w-md items-center justify-center">
```
